According to a report by Intel Market Research, the global Clip-On Thermal Sight (Day/Night Conversion) Market was valued at USD 1.32 billion in 2025 and is projected to grow from USD 1.38 billion in 2026 to USD 2.04 billion by 2034, expanding at a CAGR of 4.9% during the forecast period. The market is witnessing steady growth due to increasing defense modernization initiatives, rising investments in advanced electro-optical technologies, and growing demand for modular thermal imaging systems across military, law enforcement, and border security organizations worldwide.
Clip-on thermal sights are designed to convert existing daytime optical sights into thermal imaging systems without requiring re-zeroing, enabling users to operate effectively in darkness, smoke, fog, and other low-visibility conditions. Continuous improvements in uncooled infrared sensor technology, image resolution, and power efficiency have significantly enhanced the performance of these systems while reducing weight and improving operational flexibility. These technological advancements are encouraging 
procurement across defense agencies seeking cost-effective modernization of existing optical equipment.
